ployment#migrations","content":"`sessions`"},"370":{"id":"/operate/deployment-91","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#migrations","content":"Run migrations manually in production:"},"371":{"id":"/operate/deployment-92","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#migrations","content":"Inside the published container image, run the compiled migration entrypoint from the ingest service workdir:"},"372":{"id":"/operate/deployment-93","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#migrations","content":"The runner substitutes `{{DATABASE}}` with `CLICKHOUSE_DATABASE`. The database name must be a valid ClickHouse identifier."},"373":{"id":"/operate/deployment-94","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#cors-and-source-validation","content":"Browser traffic must come from an allowed origin. Configure `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` with the exact scheme, host, and port used by your app, for example:"},"374":{"id":"/operate/deployment-95","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#cors-and-source-validation","content":"Backend requests often omit `Origin`. They are accepted when they send one of the configured `PUBLIC_API_KEYS`. To disable no-origin backend ingest, leave `PUBLIC_API_KEYS` empty."},"375":{"id":"/operate/deployment-96","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"The ingest service has no local runtime state and can be scaled horizontally for event capture. All instances must share:"},"376":{"id":"/operate/deployment-97","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"the same ClickHouse database,"},"377":{"id":"/operate/deployment-98","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"the same accepted API keys when backend ingest uses them,"},"378":{"id":"/operate/deployment-99","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"the same origin policy,"},"379":{"id":"/operate/deployment-100","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"the same request limits."},"380":{"id":"/operate/deployment-101","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"ClickHouse write capacity is the primary scaling boundary. Keep batch sizes moderate and prefer SDK batching over one request per event for high-volume browser apps."},"381":{"id":"/operate/deployment-102","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#scaling","content":"Identity side effects (`$identify`, `$set`, `$set_once`, and `$create_alias`) are stored in ClickHouse versioned rows. That model works well for normal SDK traffic, but strict first-write-wins `$set_once` semantics can race if many replicas process identity updates for the same distinct ID at exactly the same time. For identity-heavy production workloads, either keep identity traffic on one ingest replica or route identity requests consistently until the deployment has been load-tested with your concurrency profile."},"382":{"id":"/operate/deployment-103","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#clickhouse-version-upgrades","content":"For local development, update the Compose image only after checking the current stable ClickHouse server tag and running the full verifier. For production, upgrade ClickHouse separately from the ingest service, run migrations against a staging database first, and verify the starter queries in `clickhouse-schema.md` before promoting the version."},"383":{"id":"/operate/deployment-104","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#github-pages-docs","content":"The docs are a static Fumadocs/Next app in `apps/docs` with curated content under `content/docs`. GitHub Pages builds the app with `output: 'export'` and deploys the static `apps/docs/out` tree through `.github/workflows/pages.yml`."},"384":{"id":"/operate/deployment-105","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#github-pages-docs","content":"In the repository settings, configure:"},"385":{"id":"/operate/deployment-106","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#github-pages-docs","content":"**Pages > Build and deployment > Source**: GitHub Actions."},"386":{"id":"/operate/deployment-107","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#github-pages-docs","content":"Pushes to `main` that change docs app files, `content/docs/**`, `openapi/**`, generated reference output, the lockfile, or the Pages workflow rebuild and deploy the docs site."},"387":{"id":"/operate/deployment-108","page_id":"/operate/deployment","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/deployment#github-pages-docs","content":"Same-repository pull requests get a docs preview when the PR changes docs and the latest push also touched docs-related files. The workflow publishes previews under `/pr-preview/pr-<number>/`, upserts one bot comment with the preview URL, and removes the preview when the PR is closed, merged, converted back to draft, or no longer changes docs."},"388":{"id":"/operate/helm","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"page","content":"Helm Deployment","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Operate"],"tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm"},"389":{"id":"/operate/helm-0","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm","content":"Install the ingest service on Kubernetes with autoscaling."},"390":{"id":"/operate/helm-1","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm#helm-deployment","content":"Helm Deployment"},"391":{"id":"/operate/helm-2","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm#render-locally","content":"Render Locally"},"392":{"id":"/operate/helm-3","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm#install","content":"Install"},"393":{"id":"/operate/helm-4","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Autoscaling Defaults"},"394":{"id":"/operate/helm-5","page_id":"/operate/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/helm#migrations","content":"Migrations"},"395":{"id":"/operate/helm-6","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#helm-deployment","content":"The Helm chart in `deploy/helm/clickhouse-product-analytics` deploys the ingest service to Kubernetes. It does not deploy ClickHouse. Point it at ClickHouse Cloud or an existing in-cluster ClickHouse service."},"396":{"id":"/operate/helm-7","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#install","content":"Use an existing Kubernetes secret for ClickHouse credentials when possible:"},"397":{"id":"/operate/helm-8","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#install","content":"The existing secret must contain keys named `username` and `password` unless you override `clickhouse.existingSecretUserKey` and `clickhouse.existingSecretPasswordKey`."},"398":{"id":"/operate/helm-9","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#install","content":"Use `image.tag=latest` only for quick trials. Production rollouts should use the `sha-<commit>` tag published by the container workflow or a digest-pinned image:"},"399":{"id":"/operate/helm-10","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#install","content":"`clickhouse.url` is required. Rendering fails early when it is missing so an invalid deployment is not applied. Set `ingest.publicApiKeys` to a comma-separated list when backend or no-origin ingest is enabled; browser-only deployments that rely on `ingest.allowedOrigins` can omit API keys."},"400":{"id":"/operate/helm-11","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Autoscaling is enabled by default:"},"401":{"id":"/operate/helm-12","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Value"},"402":{"id":"/operate/helm-13","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Default"},"403":{"id":"/operate/helm-14","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.minReplicas`"},"404":{"id":"/operate/helm-15","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`2`"},"405":{"id":"/operate/helm-16","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.maxReplicas`"},"406":{"id":"/operate/helm-17","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`10`"},"407":{"id":"/operate/helm-18","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.targetCPUUtilizationPercentage`"},"408":{"id":"/operate/helm-19","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`70`"},"409":{"id":"/operate/helm-20","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage`"},"410":{"id":"/operate/helm-21","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`80`"},"411":{"id":"/operate/helm-22","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"The chart also sets resource requests and limits so the HPA has stable utilization signals. Tune these values after observing real traffic and ClickHouse insert latency."},"412":{"id":"/operate/helm-23","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#migrations","content":"Run migrations from a checkout before deploying a new schema:"},"413":{"id":"/operate/helm-24","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#migrations","content":"For a Kubernetes-only network path, run a one-off pod or job with the same image and environment variables, then execute the compiled migration entrypoint from the image:"},"414":{"id":"/operate/helm-25","page_id":"/operate/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/helm#migrations","content":"Production charts default `MIGRATE_ON_START` to `false` so every replica does not attempt schema migration on startup."},"415":{"id":"/operate/railway","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"page","content":"Railway Deployment","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Operate"],"tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway"},"416":{"id":"/operate/railway-0","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway","content":"Deploy the ingest service on Railway with ClickHouse or ClickHouse Cloud."},"417":{"id":"/operate/railway-1","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#railway-deployment","content":"Railway Deployment"},"418":{"id":"/operate/railway-2","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#recommended-shape","content":"Recommended Shape"},"419":{"id":"/operate/railway-3","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#container-source","content":"Container Source"},"420":{"id":"/operate/railway-4","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#environment-variables","content":"Environment Variables"},"421":{"id":"/operate/railway-5","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#migrations","content":"Migrations"},"422":{"id":"/operate/railway-6","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#health-check","content":"Health Check"},"423":{"id":"/operate/railway-7","page_id":"/operate/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/railway#template-status","content":"Template Status"},"424":{"id":"/operate/railway-8","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway#railway-deployment","content":"Railway can run the ingest service container and connect it to ClickHouse Cloud or to a ClickHouse instance reachable from Railway. The repo does not need Railway-specific code; the service is configured entirely with environment variables."},"425":{"id":"/operate/railway-9","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway#recommended-shape","content":"Use one Railway service for the ingest container and an external ClickHouse database. ClickHouse Cloud is the simplest production target because it provides a managed HTTPS endpoint, user, password, and database. A self-managed ClickHouse service also works if Railway can reach its HTTP interface."},"426":{"id":"/operate/railway-10","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway#container-source","content":"Use the Dockerfile at:"},"427":{"id":"/operate/railway-11","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway#container-source","content":"After the GitHub Container Registry workflow has run on `main`, Railway can also deploy the published image:"},"428":{"id":"/operate/railway-12","page_id":"/operate/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/railway#container-source","content":"Use `latest` only for quick trials. Production deployments should use the `sha-<commit>` tag for the commit that passed CI or the digest-pinned GHCR reference `ghcr.io/<owner>/<repo>/ingest-service@sha256:<digest>`."},"429":{"id":"/operate/railway-13","page_id":"/operate/railw